# Bug Report: Multi-Hobby Selection Prevents Form Submission

---

**Project:** Loady QA Assignment - DemoQA Practice Form  
**Reported By:** Your Name  
**Date:** 2025-06-07  
**Severity:** High  
**Priority:** High  
**Environment:**  
- Browser: Chrome 114.0  
- OS: Windows 10 / macOS 13  
- URL: https://demoqa.com/automation-practice-form

---

## Summary

When selecting more than one hobby on the DemoQA Automation Practice Form, the form cannot be submitted. An error occurs, preventing successful submission.

---

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Navigate to https://demoqa.com/automation-practice-form  
2. Fill all required fields with valid data.  
3. Select multiple hobbies checkboxes (e.g., Sports and Music).  
4. Attempt to submit the form by clicking the Submit button.

---

## Expected Result

The form should submit successfully, and a confirmation or success message should appear.

---

## Actual Result

Form submission fails with an error message, or the form does not submit at all when multiple hobbies are selected.

---

## Impact

Blocks users from submitting the form if they select more than one hobby, limiting functionality and user experience.

---

## Notes

- Single hobby selection works correctly.  
- Issue reproducible consistently on Chrome and Firefox.

---

## Suggested Severity & Priority

- Severity: High (functional blocker)  
- Priority: High (needs timely fix)

---

## Attachments

- Screenshot or screen recording showing the error (if available).

---
